<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101359970495519></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101359970495519><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=101359970495519>levelling</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=101359970495519#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=124427><span id= >Yaninya</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>10 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Feb 13th 7:31 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Quick guide to levelling fast..at least till 40 where I am now...<br><br>A Hie mage, so was born in Felwithe...put as many points as I could into int and the balance into agility...<br><br>Fight outside Felwithe till L4 and the first pet.&nbsp;&nbsp;Slow, I know, but it's worth it.  Then off to the Kekethin newbie killing grounds for a quick jump to 5.  Off then to Butcherblocks and kill skunks, snakes etc; increasing to scarabs, skels and drakes as you rise in levels.  You may need to support your pet here a little in tanking, but the offence/defence skill rises are well worth it in later levels.  This will keep you happy to L9.<br><br>At L9, buy the water pet and go to EC.  Kill darkweed snakes especially since very few others will be bothering them (but keep an eye out for lions just in case as they tend to attack without warning).  The water pet being immune to poison, you merely need to heal it and nuke the snake a little.  At 12 or 13, go to EK and bind by the Gorge zone.<br><br>Solo bullnose snakes, carrion spiders and other lowish level stuff but stay away from gorge hounds and dark stalkers till at least L16 and the new pet.  At 16+, go kill those, one at a time.  If you are brave you can take out crag spiders at 16 with a full bar of mana, but those are better killed at 18 when resists due to level are much lower.  If introuble, gate to the bind point and run into the zone.  No point in dying if you don't have to.<br><br>At 20 (gorge hounds and crags will easily take you to 20 fast) go to Highkeep and try to get goblin groups in the basement.  If you can't, med to full, invis up, go to the jail cell, summon pet (water by preference for damage output and hps) and then kill the two prisoners to get them out of the way.  Then kill Osargen.  Let the pet tank most of the fight but keep it healed and hit Ossie with a nuke or two late in the fight to outdamage the pet and get the xps. Ossie is on a 6 minute cycle, so plenty of time to med between fights.  The prisoners are on a 5.25 minute cycle, I think.  Ossie solo will get you to 29 or 30 very comfortably.  No cash, or very little, but you won't need much at this stage and the xps are very quick.<br><br>At 29+ head to SK and solo harriers and avos, or grab a gnoll spire and solo gnolls.  Either (with a water pet) is quite easy so long as you stand a way back from the pet when you nuke and not next to it.  Standing by the pet when you nuke is a guaranteed call for a cleric...  Stick to single targets by preference and don't be afraid to gate if you get doubles you can't handle.  Gnolls when you are 31+ are magic xps and pay brilliantly.<br><br>At 37 or so when they green out, head to the Rathe Mountains and take on Cynthia at the gypsy camp (if you can get her) with a fully buffed pet, either water or fire by preference.  If you can, get a giant group but for some reason mages aren't well loved in groups so you will mostly be solo.  Cynthia will take you through 42 easily and quickly.  You could go kill the solo spectre in the Feerrott if you prefer, though for that I use a fire pet and keep it healed.  If you want to kill clops solo, wait for the 39 pets...the 34 pets don't have the hps to stand up to clops.  From then on, the world is your oyster...<br><br>Velious and the dire wolves are a good target, or Luclin and some of its zones...Stay away from Kunark if you can as their mobs have mega hitpoints for the xps gained, and you will more often than not have to use a large amount of mana to kill the stuff.  The old world is by far the best (imho) for fast levelling, moderate mana useage and minimal deaths.  I will be staying in the Rathe Mountains and killing Cynthia till 44 when I will go to visit the troll guards and try to get them to see the error of their ways.  At 48 when the guards green out, it's finally off to Velious for me.<br><br>If you can get groups with your guild or friends, then disregard a lot of what I say, but if you solo for whatever reason, the above has worked for me.  After going to EK at L11, I died once there, twice in the Keep to goblins (once my fault, once to a bad group pull), once in SK when the undead cyclops snuck up on me, and twice in the Rathe Mountains when I was the preferred meal for hill giants due to enthusiastic overnuking  :)  <br><br>And the best time you will have is with the L34 Summon Monster spell...I used nothing but that between 34 and 38 and it was the greatest time. <br><br>Hope this helps...<br>Jacynth deVichier<br>L40 mage (unguilded)<br>The Rathe<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
