<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101422892131319></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101422892131319><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=101422892131319>RE: levelling</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=101422892131319#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=113580><span id= >Kranken</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>9 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Feb 20th 1:16 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>An okay guide, but I would like to mention a few things. Not flaming ya, just wanted to point some things out<br><br>I have no idea why anyone would want to hunt in SK past level 29, as the experience slows down rather radically from what I have seen at those levels. Maybe you *can* level there, just not worth the effort IMHO. Dalnir all the way in those levels--if you can get a group there the levels fly past, typically 1 yellow in 25-30 minutes, no joke.<br>I really wouldn't fight Cynthia, she is rather dangerous to stand up and fight, and you can get experiance more than twice as good in the Thurgadin mines. If you really want to fight her I wouldn't even use a pet, just pop off 2 cinder bolts from maximum range and she should either die or start walking away. The Overthere is also good for these levels in a good group, but Thurgadin is amazing. Overthere, however, is the best place I've seen to get through hell level 40, I got through in right around 10 hours. Past that the Dreadlands tundra yeti caves are some very easy levels as early as 39 if you want to try them.<br><br>A note on pet usage--I used fire for all the places I recommended, since it chews into all the mobs very fast and you need to nuke far less due to the mega damage shield.<br><br>Sorry to complain about your guide, it is better then many that are posted here.Thanks for tolerating The Amazing Antisocial Gnome.<br><br>Kranken, 51 elementalist<br>&lt;Order of Seibwen&gt;<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
